      • packComparable

        public static byte[] packComparable(List<byte[]> arrays,
                    byte delimiter,
                    byte terminalDelimiter)
        note: the values delimiter and terminalDelimiter must not only NOT appear in the byte[], but be less than any other value in the byte array. Defaults used in helper methods are 0 and 1. These values in the packed byte[] to make it comparable as an unsigned byte [] A future extension would use duplication/padding (0 -> 00, 00 -> 000, etc) in order to handle this, but it's not needed yet. In practice, the byte values are for printable ascii chars and binary data may be base64 encoded as long as all values are byte values > 1
        Parameters:
        arrays - array of byte[] to pack
        delimiter - recommend 0
        terminalDelimiter - recommend 1
        Returns:
